# 📘 Section 4: Structural Diagrams & Schematics

## 4.1 Swing Control Class Hierarchy

```mermaid
graph TD
    A[java lang Object] --> B[java awt Component]
    B --> C[java awt Container]
    C --> D[javax swing JComponent]
    D --> D1[JLabel]
    D --> D2[JButton]
    D --> D3[JTextField]
    D --> D4[JTextArea]
    D --> D5[JCheckBox]
    D --> D6[JRadioButton]
    D --> D7[JComboBox]
    D --> D8[JList]
    D --> D9[JSlider]
    D --> D10[JProgressBar]
    D --> D11[JScrollPane]
    D --> D12[JMenuBar]
    D --> D13[JTable]
    D --> D14[JTree]
    D --> D15[JTabbedPane]
    D --> D16[JOptionPane]
    D12 --> E[JMenu]
    E --> F[JMenuItem]
    D11 --> G[Hosts]
    G --> D3
    G --> D4
    G --> D8
    G --> D13
```

## 4.2 The 5-Step "Lifecycle" of a Swing Control

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A[Step 1: Declare reference] --> B[Step 2: Instantiate with constructor]
    B --> C[Step 3: Configure via setters - bounds font color]
    C --> D[Step 4: Register Event Listener]
    D --> E[Step 5: add to Container JFrame JPanel]
    E --> F[Call setVisible true on top-level container]
    F --> G[EDT paints component and dispatches events]
```

## 4.3 Event Listener Routing Architecture

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    User((User Action)) -->|Click Drag Type| Comp[Swing Control e.g. JButton]
    Comp -->|Fires| Evt[Event Object e.g. ActionEvent]
    Evt -->|Dispatched to| Reg[Registered Listener e.g. ActionListener]
    Reg -->|Invokes callback| CB[actionPerformed method]
    CB -->|Reads/Writes| Model[Control Model]
    CB -->|Updates UI| View[Component repaint]
    Model -.->|Triggers repaint| View
```

## 4.4 Radio Button Grouping — Why `ButtonGroup` Matters

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    subgraph WithoutButtonGroup
        X1[Radio A] --- X2[Radio B]
        X3[Radio C] --- X4[All can be selected simultaneously]
    end
    subgraph WithButtonGroup
        Y1[Radio A] -->|deselects| Y2[Radio B]
        Y2 -->|deselects| Y3[Radio C]
        Y3 -->|deselects| Y1
    end
```

## 4.5 Container-to-Control Attachment Block Diagram

```mermaid
graph TD
    JF[JFrame - top level window] --> CP[Content Pane - default Container]
    CP --> LM[Layout Manager - FlowLayout etc]
    CP --> P1[JPanel 1]
    CP --> P2[JPanel 2]
    P1 --> LM1[Inner Layout e.g. GridLayout]
    P2 --> LM2[Inner Layout e.g. BorderLayout]
    P1 --> C1[JLabel]
    P1 --> C2[JTextField]
    P1 --> C3[JButton]
    P2 --> C4[JTable inside JScrollPane]
    P2 --> C5[JCheckBox group]
```

