> 4. **Not wrapping `JTextArea` in a `JScrollPane`** — long output gets clipped; examiner deducts 0.5 mark.
> 5. **Forgetting to call `add()` for every control** — the control is created but never displayed, so the program "doesn't work". Lose 0.5–1 mark.
> 6. **Using `null` layout and absolute `setBounds(x,y,w,h)`** — this is *legal* but considered poor practice; KTU prefers `LayoutManager` use. Some examiners deduct partial marks.
> 7. **Mistaking `addActionListener(this)` for a constructor call** — `this` refers to the class itself, which must `implements ActionListener` and override `actionPerformed()`. Forgetting the override = compile error = **0 marks** for that question.
> 8. **Using `getText()` on `JPasswordField`** — deprecated, will lose marks. Always use `getPassword()`.

