### 3.3 Derivation 3 — Layout Managers (A Comparison Program)

**Problem:** Demonstrate the use of `BorderLayout` and `GridLayout` in a single Swing app.

#### Step-by-Step Construction:

```java
import javax.swing.*;
import java.awt.*;

public class LayoutDemo extends JFrame {
    public LayoutDemo() {
        setTitle("Layout Manager Demo");
        setSize(500, 400);
        setDefaultCloseOperation(EXIT_ON_CLOSE);

        // ===== Panel 1: BorderLayout =====
        JPanel borderPanel = new JPanel(new BorderLayout(5, 5));
        borderPanel.setBorder(BorderFactory.createTitledBorder("BorderLayout"));
        borderPanel.add(new JButton("NORTH"),  BorderLayout.NORTH);
        borderPanel.add(new JButton("SOUTH"),  BorderLayout.SOUTH);
        borderPanel.add(new JButton("EAST"),   BorderLayout.EAST);
        borderPanel.add(new JButton("WEST"),   BorderLayout.WEST);
        borderPanel.add(new JButton("CENTER"), BorderLayout.CENTER);

        // ===== Panel 2: GridLayout (3 rows x 2 cols) =====
        JPanel gridPanel = new JPanel(new GridLayout(3, 2, 5, 5));
        gridPanel.setBorder(BorderFactory.createTitledBorder("GridLayout 3x2"));
        gridPanel.add(new JButton("Btn 1"));
        gridPanel.add(new JButton("Btn 2"));
        gridPanel.add(new JButton("Btn 3"));
        gridPanel.add(new JButton("Btn 4"));
        gridPanel.add(new JButton("Btn 5"));
        gridPanel.add(new JButton("Btn 6"));

        // ===== Add both panels to the Frame's BorderLayout =====
        setLayout(new BorderLayout(10, 10));
        add(borderPanel, BorderLayout.CENTER);
        add(gridPanel,   BorderLayout.SOUTH);

        setVisible(true);
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        SwingUtilities.invokeLater(() -> new LayoutDemo());
    }
}
```

> **[!TIP]**
> **Analysis:** Notice how a `JPanel` (which is itself a container) uses one layout, and is then placed inside a parent (`JFrame`) that uses a *different* layout. This **nesting of layouts** is the standard professional way to build complex UIs in Swing.

