### 3.4 Analytical Matrix — `JCheckBox` vs `JRadioButton` vs `JComboBox` vs `JList`

| **Component** | **Selection Type** | **Multi-Select?** | **Requires Container Class?** | **Best Use Case** |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| `JCheckBox` | Toggle (binary on/off) | ✅ Yes (independent toggles) | No | Toggling settings (e.g., "Show notifications") |
| `JRadioButton` | Mutually exclusive (only one in group) | ❌ No (needs `ButtonGroup`) | `ButtonGroup` | Gender, Yes/No, single-choice questions |
| `JComboBox<E>` | Drop-down selection | ❌ No (single select by default) | No (built-in drop-down) | Country selection, large option lists in small space |
| `JList<E>` | Scrollable list | ✅ Yes (with `MULTIPLE_INTERVAL_SELECTION`) | Usually `JScrollPane` | Selecting files, items, multi-choice options |

#### Code Snippet for `JRadioButton` with `ButtonGroup`:

```java
JRadioButton male   = new JRadioButton("Male");
JRadioButton female = new JRadioButton("Female");

ButtonGroup genderGroup = new ButtonGroup();
genderGroup.add(male);
genderGroup.add(female);
```

> **Why this matters:** `ButtonGroup` is **not a visual container** — it does not display anything. It is a *logical* container that enforces mutual exclusion between its member `AbstractButton` components.

