### **Topic Recap & Important Things to Remember (Rapid Revision Checklist)**

> **[!IMPORTANT]**
> **High-Yield Revision Bullets for Last-Minute Reading:**

- 📌 **Swing is in `javax.swing`**, NOT `java.awt`. Import it with `import javax.swing.*;`.
- 📌 **The "J" Prefix Rule:** Every Swing component's class name starts with the letter `J` (e.g., `JButton`, `JFrame`, `JLabel`).
- 📌 **Lightweight vs Heavyweight:** All Swing components are lightweight **EXCEPT** the four top-level containers: `JFrame`, `JDialog`, `JWindow`, `JApplet` (deprecated).
- 📌 **MVC Pattern:** Swing components follow Model-View-Controller — data (`ListModel`, `TableModel`), display (UI Delegate), and event handling (`ActionListener`) are separated.
- 📌 **EDT Rule:** GUI code MUST run on the Event Dispatch Thread. Always wrap your GUI construction in `SwingUtilities.invokeLater(() -> { ... });`.
- 📌 **`JFrame` Default Layout:** The content pane of a `JFrame` uses `BorderLayout` by default. The 5 regions are `NORTH`, `SOUTH`, `EAST`, `WEST`, `CENTER`.
- 📌 **Setting L&F:** Use `UIManager.setLookAndFeel(className)` **before** creating any component. To get the system's native look, use `UIManager.getSystemLookAndFeelClassName()`.
- 📌 **Event Listener Interfaces:** `ActionListener` (buttons, menu items), `ItemListener` (checkboxes, radio buttons), `MouseListener`/`MouseMotionListener` (mouse events), `KeyListener` (keyboard), `WindowListener` (window events).
- 📌 **`ButtonGroup` is a LOGICAL container**, not a visual one — it forces mutual exclusion between its member `AbstractButton` components but does not display anything.
- 📌 **Always wrap `JTextArea` in `JScrollPane`** if you want scrollbars (`add(new JScrollPane(textArea))`).
- 📌 **`JOptionPane` Static Methods:** `showMessageDialog()`, `showConfirmDialog()`, `showInputDialog()`, `showOptionDialog()` for standard dialog boxes.
- 📌 **`setDefaultCloseOperation(JFrame.EXIT_ON_CLOSE)`** is mandatory in standalone apps, otherwise JVM stays alive after window close.
- 📌 **Content Pane:** `JFrame` is a multi-layered root pane. You add components to `frame.getContentPane().add(...)` — this is a key KTU point.
- 📌 **`JTable` Constructor:** `JTable(Object[][] rowData, Object[] columnNames)`.
- 📌 **`JTree` Constructor:** `JTree(Object[] nodes)` or `JTree(TreeNode root)`.
- 📌 **`BoxLayout` axes:** `BoxLayout.X_AXIS` (horizontal row), `BoxLayout.Y_AXIS` (vertical column).
- 📌 **CardLayout methods:** `cardLayout.show(container, name)` and `cardLayout.next(container)` to switch cards programmatically.
