## 5.1 PART A — Short Answer Questions (3 Marks Each)

### Question A1 `[KTU University Exam – May 2024 Model]`
**Explain the class hierarchy of Swing buttons. List any four methods of `AbstractButton` common to all of them.**

**Model Answer (3 marks):**
1. **Hierarchy (1½ marks):** All Swing buttons inherit from `javax.swing.AbstractButton`, which extends `JComponent` → `Container` → `Component` → `Object`. Concrete subclasses are `JButton`, `JToggleButton`, `JCheckBox`, and `JRadioButton`. Menu variants `JMenuItem`, `JCheckBoxMenuItem`, and `JRadioButtonMenuItem` also extend `AbstractButton`.
2. **Common methods (1½ marks, any 4):** `setText(String)`, `setIcon(Icon)`, `setMnemonic(char)`, `setEnabled(boolean)`, `addActionListener(ActionListener)`, `addItemListener(ItemListener)`, `isSelected()`, `setActionCommand(String)`.

### Question A2 `[KTU University Exam – Dec 2023 Model]`
**Differentiate between `JCheckBox` and `JRadioButton`. When is `ButtonGroup` used?**

**Model Answer (3 marks):**
- **`JCheckBox`** is used for **multiple, independent** selections (e.g., selecting multiple pizza toppings).
- **`JRadioButton`** is used for **mutually-exclusive** selection (e.g., choosing gender).
- **`ButtonGroup`** is used to logically group `JRadioButton` (or `JToggleButton`) instances so that selecting one **automatically deselects** the others. It is a non-visual container.

