## 5.3 ⚠️ KTU Examiner's Valuation Warning / Pitfall Callout

> [!WARNING]
> **Common mistakes costing 2-3 marks each:**
> 1. **Forgetting `setDefaultCloseOperation(EXIT_ON_CLOSE)`** — the program runs but won't close cleanly, which examiners treat as a half-finished answer.
> 2. **Adding `ButtonGroup` to a `JFrame`** — this is a **compilation error**; students lose a full mark for misunderstanding that `ButtonGroup` is not a `Component`.
> 3. **Using `e.getActionCommand()` without calling `setActionCommand(String)`** — returns `null`. Either pre-set the command *or* use `e.getSource() == buttonReference`.
> 4. **Confusing `ActionListener` and `ItemListener`** — `ActionListener` fires on *activation* (mouse release while inside the button); `ItemListener` fires on *state change* (the `isSelected()` flag flips). Toggle/Check/Radio use **both**.
> 5. **Not calling `setVisible(true)`** — window never appears; examiner marks zero for output even if code is correct.
> 6. **Mixing `AWT (java.awt.Button)` with `Swing (javax.swing.JButton)`** — disallowed in 2024 Scheme questions. Always use **`javax.swing.JButton`**.

