> [!WARNING]
> **Common Mistakes That Cost Marks in KTU 2024 Exams:**
>
> 1. **Forgetting `addActionListener` registration** — Students write the listener class but forget to call `component.addActionListener(...)`. **Penalty: 2–3 marks.**
> 2. **Using AWT `TextField` instead of Swing `JTextField`** when the question specifies "Swing" — **Penalty: 1–2 marks (compilation error).**
> 3. **Omitting `@Override` annotation** — not fatal, but KTU evaluators may deduct 0.5 mark for missing override marker.
> 4. **Not using `SwingUtilities.invokeLater()` for the main launch** — Considered a best-practice violation; 1 mark deduction in stricter evaluations.
> 5. **Confusing `getText()` with `getName()`** — `getName()` returns the component's identifier (a programmer-set string); `getText()` returns the user-entered content. **Very common mistake.**
> 6. **Implementing all 7 methods of `WindowListener` instead of using `WindowAdapter`** — wastes time; 1–2 marks lost for unnecessary code.
> 7. **Forgetting to handle `NumberFormatException`** when parsing text-field input — produces runtime crashes; **2-mark penalty** if question explicitly demands exception handling.
> 8. **Not clearing the text field / refocusing it** after action — minor UI issue but signals incomplete implementation.
> 9. **Setting layout to `null` and using `setBounds` without question requirement** — works but is bad practice; KTU prefers layout managers.
> 10. **Forgetting `setVisible(true)`** — Program compiles but nothing appears on screen; full functionality lost.

