## 5.4 Topic Recap & Important Things to Remember (Rapid Revision Checklist)

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Last-Minute KTU Revision — Memorize These:**

- [ ] **`JTextField` is in `javax.swing`** — NOT `java.awt`. Always import `javax.swing.JTextField`.
- [ ] **Most-used constructor:** `JTextField(int columns)` — for predictable UI width.
- [ ] **Most-used methods:** `getText()`, `setText()`, `setColumns()`, `setEditable(boolean)`, `setHorizontalAlignment(int)`, `addActionListener()`.
- [ ] **A `JTextField` fires `ActionEvent` on the Enter key** — this is the SYLLABUS-MANDATED link between `JTextField` and event handling.
- [ ] **Delegation Event Model = Source + Listener + Event Object** — three players, three marks minimum in any theory question.
- [ ] **Listener registration is mandatory:** `source.addXListener(listenerObj)`. Without this, no events are processed.
- [ ] **Listener interfaces** (Java 8+ allow lambdas for single-method ones): `ActionListener` (1 method), `KeyListener` (3), `MouseListener` (5), `MouseMotionListener` (2), `WindowListener` (7), `FocusListener` (2), `ItemListener` (1), `TextListener` (1).
- [ ] **Adapter classes** exist for multi-method listeners: `KeyAdapter`, `MouseAdapter`, `MouseMotionAdapter`, `WindowAdapter`, `FocusAdapter`. **No adapter for `ActionListener`** (only 1 method).
- [ ] **Event classes** are in `java.awt.event` (or `javax.swing.event` for Swing-specific events). All extend `java.util.EventObject`.
- [ ] **Event dispatch happens on the EDT** — always use `SwingUtilities.invokeLater(Runnable)` to launch a Swing app.
- [ ] **`e.getSource()` on an `ActionEvent`** returns the originating component — useful when one listener is shared across many sources.
- [ ] **Anonymous inner class syntax:** `new ActionListener() { @Override public void actionPerformed(ActionEvent e) { ... } }` — memorize verbatim.
- [ ] **Lambda syntax (Java 8+) for single-method listeners:** `btn.addActionListener(e -> label.setText("Hi"));` — cleaner, exam-friendly.
- [ ] **Do NOT mix AWT and Swing in the same top-level container** — `JFrame` should contain only `JComponents` (JButton, JLabel, JTextField, JPanel).
- [ ] **`setDefaultCloseOperation(JFrame.EXIT_ON_CLOSE)`** is the simplest way to terminate on close. For controlled closing, use `DO_NOTHING_ON_CLOSE` + `WindowAdapter`.
- [ ] **`try-catch` around `Integer.parseInt(textField.getText())`** is the standard way to handle invalid numeric input.
- [ ] **KEEP `JTextField` and `JLabel` as instance fields** (not local variables) so the listener can access them.
- [ ] **Always override `actionPerformed` / `keyPressed` etc. with the EXACT signature** — even a `throws` clause change causes compile error.

> **Final Exam Mantra:** *"JTextField gives you the data. The Listener gives it meaning. The EventObject delivers it. Together, they form the Delegation Event Model."*
